textAnnotations.description:
WILL YOUR CHURCH NAVIGATE THESE CHANGES?
a book for those who will lead congregations in challenging times.
radoxy helps you understand and explain what's happening,
gives everyone a chance to speak and be heard,
and moves you into the future as one body, together.
xy resonates with my own experience. When the intention of people
site sides is to connect, not to win, they can bring forward the best of
ves. Deep human connection takes place in the presence of profound
ement. It is a holy mystery.'
-Mary Jacksteit, JD, MS, Project Manager,
Public Conversations Project
KEN HOWARD is an expert in organizational development and
conflict resolution. He has been an ordained priest in the Episcopal
Church since 1993, and holds a Master of Divinity degree from Virginia
Theological Seminary, with an emphasis on Church History, and a
Master of Education Degree from Virginia Commonwealth University,
with an emphasis on Adult Education. Ken is respected and trusted for
ility to build consensus groups with opposing theological and political views, and has
called upon to facilitate dialogs on a wide range of issues.
AN MCLAREN is a speaker, pastor, and networker among innovative Christian
ers, and author of A Generous Orthodoxy and other books.
E VERY REV. DR. PAUL F. M. ZAHL is Dean and President Emeritus, Trinity
pol for Ministry, Ambridge, PA, and Rector Emeritus of All Saints Episcopal Church,
evy Chase, MD. He is the author of Who Will Deliver Us? and other books.
